.TH "vfs_fsync" 9 "vfs_fsync" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vfs_fsync \- perform a fsync or fdatasync on a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vfs_fsync
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "int datasync "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
file to sync
.IP "datasync" 12
only perform a fdatasync operation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write back data and metadata for \fIfile\fP to disk.  If \fIdatasync\fP is
set only metadata needed to access modified file data is written.
